  <thing id="cInqS2SunS" name="Sun Strike" description="At 5th level, a hunter of the dead can infuse a single weapon she wields with the purifying light of the sun as a swift action for a number of rounds per day equal to her inquisitor level. These rounds do not need to be consecutive. While a weapon is infused with the sun, it deals +1d6 points of damage to any creature that is susceptible or vulnerable to sunlight, including many types of undead (particularly spectres, vampires, and wraiths). This additional damage also applies to oozes and fungus-based monsters. A weapon infused with sun strike sheds illumination as if it were a sunrod." compset="ClSpecial">
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Attack"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="Tracker"/>
    <tag group="Usage" tag="DayRound"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ClExLose"/>
    <eval phase="Final" priority="10000"><![CDATA[~ If we're not shown, just get out now
doneif (tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] = 0)

field[abDuration].value += field[xAllLev].value

field[abValue].value += 1
field[livename].text = field[thingname].text & " +" & field[abValue].value & "d6"]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cInqS2OaU" name="Oath Against Undeath" description="A hunter of the dead with this oath vows to restore the natural state of death to any animate corpse she encounters, and destroy the undead energy in the process. While a few hunter of the dead who take this oath recognize that not all undead are evil, others are quite willing to purge neutral and good undead along with all the evil ones.\n\n{b}Code of Conduct{/b}\nDestroy all undead. Put to rest the poor souls turned against their will. Prevent the taint of undeath from spreading to the newly dead, blessing or burning the corpses as necessary." compset="ClSpecial">
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ClExLose"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioS2AugMW" name="Augment Crystal, Masterwork" description="An augment crystal is a small gem, crystal, or similar object that provides a magical effect when affixed to a weapon, shield, or suit of armor. Each item can hold a single augment crystal, but an attached crystal can be swapped for another one at any time. Attaching an augment crystal to (or removing it from) an item requires a move action that doesn&#146;t provoke attacks of opportunity. This is a product of thassilonian times and the magic to create these can NO longer be duplicated.\n\nThis crystal can {i}only{/i} be applied to non-masterwork weapon, armor, or shield. Doing so causes the item to become a masterwork version.\n\n{B}HL Note:{/b} Remove your non-masterwork item and add a masterwork version of the item. Then select it from the list below so you can keep track of which item this is augmenting." compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="usrCandid1" value="thingid.iMagWeapon|thingid.iMagArmor"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="300"/>
    <fieldval field="iCL" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="srcAoW"/>
    <tag group="ChooseSrc1" tag="Hero"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="iSchool" tag="Transmutat"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="AlwaysAvl"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioS2WepS" name="Weapon Crystal, Slashing" description="An augment crystal is a small gem, crystal, or similar object that provides a magical effect when affixed to a weapon. Each item can hold a single weapon crystal, but an attached crystal can be swapped for another one at any time. Attaching an weapon crystal to (or removing it from) a weapon requires a move action that does not provoke attacks of opportunity. This is a product of thassilonian times and the magic to create these can NO longer be duplicated.\n\nThis crystal can be applied to both non-masterwork and masterwork weapons and doing so causes the damage type to change to Slashing only.  If placed on a bow or crossbow the projectiles become slashing regardless of the type of arrow being fired." compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="300"/>
    <fieldval field="iCL" value="1"/>
    <fieldval field="usrCandid1" value="component.BaseWep|thingid.iMagWeapon"/>
    <usesource source="srcAoW"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="iSchool" tag="Transmutat"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="AlwaysAvl"/>
    <tag group="ChooseSrc1" tag="Hero"/>
    <eval phase="First" priority="10000"><![CDATA[~ if nothing chosen get out now
doneif (field[usrChosen1].ischosen <> 1)

~ remove all old damage types and replace with Slashing
perform field[usrChosen1].chosen.delete[wType.?]
perform field[usrChosen1].chosen.assign[wType.S]]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="iS2Durinda" name="Durindana" description="{i}Durindana is an austere Bastard Sword.  Those familiar with the arts of the forge recognize the craftsmanship as dwarven, but the style of the blade is distinctly human.  A faint tracery of Celestial script runs the length of the blade, naming the weapon Durindana (meaning &quot;Light of Sarenrae&quot;) and proclaiming its role as the reliquary for the finger bones of Saint Ardtan.{/i}\n\n{i}Durindana{/i} is a blade sacred to the faith of Sarenrae, forged by a dwarf weaponsmith over a thousand years ago to house the finger bones of the legendary undead-hunter, Saint Ardtan. Ardtan was slain defending a dwarf stronghold from a plague of vampires. In gratitude for his sacrifice, the dwarf thane presented the church of Sarenrae with this sword to honor the hero. When Ardtan was canonized several years later, the hilt of the sword was hollowed out to serve as a reliquary for the saint&apos;s fingerbones. The church kept {i}Durindana{/i} in its securest vaults, allowing it to be used only by the holiest persons and only in times of dire need. Even though many of its wielders have died in battle, {i}Durindana{/i} always finds its way back into the hands of a holy warrior.\n\n+2 Bastard Sword that does an additional +1d6 points of divine damage to undead and +1d6 vs evil creatures. It also overcomes the DR of any undead it hits.\n\nDurindana&apos;s caster level is 12.\n{B}2/day{/b} - Daylight.\n{b}1/day{/b} - Magic Circle against Evil\n\n{B}Powers{/b}\n{I}Sarenrae&apos;s Baleful Eye (Su):{/I} Starting at 10th level, as long as you carry {i}Durindana{/i} before you, your channel energy gains a +2 bonus on the DC and a bonus to damage vs undead equal to your caster level. These affects only apply when you are using your channel energy to damage undead.\n\n{i}Saint&apos;s Grace (Su):{/i} {i}Durindana{/i} provides you with a +2 divine bonus on all saving throws." compset="MagicWep" summary="+1 Bastard Sword and does an additional 1d6 points of divine damage to undead" uniqueness="useronce">
