  <thing id="ioS2SWLong" name="Spellworm, Longstrider" description="A {i}spellworm{/i} imparts the ability to perform a single casting of a spell to its host.\n\n{b}Description:{/b} A {i}spellworm{/i} looks like any other Tiny Kyuss worm, save for faintly glowing arcane sigils that adorn its sickening flesh. For as long as a host creature is bound to a {i}spellworm,{/i} its pupils turn a dull and sickly green.\n\n{b}Activation:{/b} Like other Kyuss worms, a {i}spellworm{/i} must be inside a host creature in order to be used. Once a host creature has successfully taken the worm into its body, casting the stored spell is a standard-action, just like using a spell-like ability.\n\n{b}Effect:{/b} A {i}spellworm{/i} grants its host the ability to cast one spell. The host casts the spell as a full-round action. This follows the normal rules for casting the spell in question, including provoking attacks of opportunity, being subject to arcane spell failure, and any other applicable restrictions. The worm provides the power to cast the spell at the given caster level, even if the host&apos;s relevant ability score is too low to normally cast the spell, but the saving throw DC is dependant on the host&apos;s relevant ability score. Upon casting this spell the {i}spellworm{/i} it is destroyed.\n\n{B}Note:{/b} Check marking this item means you have let the worm burrow into you and it won&apos;t come out until used." compset="Wondrous">
