      </child>
    </thing>
  <thing id="iS2Aaqa" name="Sword of Aaqa" description="The {i}sword of Aaqa{/i} is a {i}+2 axiomatic mithril long sword{/i} with a hilt set with six pale sapphires the size of grapes. Used by the Wind Duke Icosiol on the battlefield of Pesh, the {i}sword of Aaqa{/i} is the companion blade to the {i}lightning sword{/i}. Whenever the wielder scores a critical hit on a creature with the {i}sword of Aaqa{/i} (even if that creature is normally immune to damage from critical hits), the sword creates a powerful blast of wind storm force wind. The creature hit can make a DC 18 Fortitude save to resist the effects of the wind. Small or smaller creatures (or flying Medium creatures) are blown away by this blast of wind. Creatures on the ground are knocked down and roll 1d4x10 feet, taking 1d4 points of nonlethal damage per 10 feet. Flying creatures are blown back 2d6x10 feet and take 2d6 points of nonlethal damage. Medium creatures (or flying Large creatures) that fail this save are knocked down. Huge (or land-bound Large) and larger creatures suffer no noticeable effect from the blast of wind.\n\nIf the wielder fights with the {i}lightning sword{/i} and the {i}sword of Aaqa{/i}, he may strike the two swords together as a standard action to generate 30-foot line of sonic energy. All creatures in this area take 6d6 sonic damage (Reflex DC 18 half ). This ability can be used three times per day." compset="MagicWep" summary="The {i}sword of Aaqa{/i} is a {i}+2 axiomatic mithril temple sword{/i}." uniqueness="useronce">
    <fieldval field="BonEnhance" value="2"/>
    <fieldval field="iCL" value="9"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="35000"/>
